I'll keep my promise to make it

1031
01:02:20,216 --> 01:02:21,551
as high as I can.

1032
01:02:37,233 --> 01:02:39,402
I'll ease your sorrow, Mom.

1033
01:02:45,241 --> 01:02:46,617
Mr. Kang…

1034
01:02:48,953 --> 01:02:50,872
That's why I chose a career in law.

1035
01:02:53,624 --> 01:02:54,876
I'm just like all of you.

1036
01:02:55,918 --> 01:02:59,672
I wanted to become a judge
who applied the law fairly to everyone

1037
01:02:59,755 --> 01:03:02,884
so that no one would feel
as if they were treated unjustly

1038
01:03:02,967 --> 01:03:05,219
like my mother was.

1039
01:03:05,303 --> 01:03:06,137
You see,

1040
01:03:06,220 --> 01:03:09,223
I'd never do anything
to embarrass my mother.

1041
01:03:10,141 --> 01:03:12,018
I have many faults as a human being.

1042
01:03:12,101 --> 01:03:13,311
But as a judge,

1043
01:03:15,479 --> 01:03:17,273
I've never crossed the line.

1044
01:03:20,610 --> 01:03:22,236
I'm sorry.

1045
01:03:23,321 --> 01:03:26,949
I didn't know what you went through.

1046
01:03:27,700 --> 01:03:30,077
I've been so mean to you.

1047
01:03:31,370 --> 01:03:33,247
I just thought you were
some despicable guy

1048
01:03:33,331 --> 01:03:35,541
who'd always been privileged
and on the fast track.

1049
01:03:37,460 --> 01:03:38,753
I understand.

1050
01:03:38,836 --> 01:03:42,673
I do look especially elegant.

1051
01:03:43,257 --> 01:03:45,092
I was right about the despicable part.

1052
01:03:46,928 --> 01:03:47,845
Mr. Kang.

1053
01:03:49,513 --> 01:03:51,974
I had no idea either.

1054
01:03:53,476 --> 01:03:55,311
It must have been so tough

1055
01:03:56,145 --> 01:03:58,189
-at such a young age.
-It's all right.

1056
01:03:58,272 --> 01:04:01,317
I'm not the only one
who's been through tough times.

1057
01:04:05,237 --> 01:04:06,739
What are you thinking so hard about?

1058
01:04:07,865 --> 01:04:09,033
At the very least,

1059
01:04:09,617 --> 01:04:11,243
you didn't recuse yourself.

1060
01:04:13,162 --> 01:04:13,996
What?

1061
01:04:15,957 --> 01:04:19,085
If you had trouble in the past
with the defendant Yoo Baek-man,

1062
01:04:20,503 --> 01:04:22,171
shouldn't you have recused yourself?

1063
01:04:24,590 --> 01:04:26,425
For a fair trial?

1064
01:04:26,509 --> 01:04:28,052
-Jun-u…
-What?

1065
01:04:29,261 --> 01:04:30,179
Am I wrong?

1066
01:04:35,059 --> 01:04:36,394
Jun-u's right.

1067
01:04:38,062 --> 01:04:38,980
Ms. Park…

1068
01:04:39,063 --> 01:04:40,940
Do you remember, Mr. Kang?

1069
01:04:42,817 --> 01:04:44,944
When I first brought up
Yoo Baek-man's name…

1070
01:04:45,027 --> 01:04:46,654
Do you know Mr. Yoo Baek-man?

1071
01:04:47,196 --> 01:04:49,615
Who is that? I don't know him.

1072
01:04:49,699 --> 01:04:51,283
You said you didn't know him.

1073
01:04:52,410 --> 01:04:55,579
-It's a name you wouldn't forget.
-Well, that's…

1074
01:04:56,080 --> 01:04:57,790
I was briefly mistaken
to suddenly hear…

1075
01:04:57,873 --> 01:05:01,085
When I suddenly mentioned
trial manipulation, how did you respond?

1076
01:05:01,168 --> 01:05:02,920
Yoo Jae-beom believes

1077
01:05:03,004 --> 01:05:05,172
that you rigged the trial.

1078
01:05:05,256 --> 01:05:06,966
That's ridiculous!

1079
01:05:07,049 --> 01:05:11,387
Do you think I'd do such a thing?
A rigged trial? What do you take me for?

1080
01:05:11,470 --> 01:05:14,640
You taught us about the instinctive
defensive mechanism of humans.

1081
01:05:15,349 --> 01:05:17,143
If it never happened,

1082
01:05:17,226 --> 01:05:19,645
she would've denied it
without any unnecessary comments.

1083
01:05:19,729 --> 01:05:23,566
"I'm not a bad person."
"Who do you think I am?" Blah, blah.

1084
01:05:23,649 --> 01:05:25,735
Making such unnecessary comments

1085
01:05:25,818 --> 01:05:29,488
is derived from the instinctive
defensive mechanism of humans.

1086
01:05:30,072 --> 01:05:30,948
That's right.

1087
01:05:32,533 --> 01:05:34,493
That long story you just told us was also…

1088
01:05:36,746 --> 01:05:40,166
You taught us back then
when we knew nothing.

1089
01:05:40,249 --> 01:05:41,917
Of course, it's your fault.

1090
01:05:42,001 --> 01:05:45,254
No matter how much you explain,
they're just motives for the crime.

1091
01:05:47,548 --> 01:05:48,674
Ms. Park.

1092
01:05:48,758 --> 01:05:52,636
The painful story you shared with us.

1093
01:05:53,554 --> 01:05:56,265
In the end, that's a strong motive.

1094
01:05:57,266 --> 01:05:58,142
Is it not?

1095
01:06:27,463 --> 01:06:28,964
I've taught you well.

1096
01:06:35,054 --> 01:06:35,888
Yes.

1097
01:06:36,597 --> 01:06:39,016
-I did it.
-Mr. Kang!

1098
01:06:39,100 --> 01:06:41,477
Did you really rig the trial?

1099
01:06:41,560 --> 01:06:43,020
Seriously?

1100
01:06:43,604 --> 01:06:45,189
Now that we're not on the same side,

1101
01:06:45,272 --> 01:06:47,441
I better exercise
my right to remain silent.

1102
01:06:53,280 --> 01:06:55,032
See you in court, everyone.

1103
01:07:24,687 --> 01:07:29,942
PRO BONO

1104
01:07:52,047 --> 01:07:54,300
-Do you have an attorney?
-I'll be representing myself.

1105
01:07:54,383 --> 01:07:56,135
Those people have nothing to do with me.

1106
01:07:56,218 --> 01:07:57,678
They're below my standard.

1107
01:07:58,929 --> 01:08:00,723
-Father?
-His father-in-law?

1108
01:08:00,806 --> 01:08:02,641
Thank goodness you went undercover!

1109
01:08:02,725 --> 01:08:03,559
You taught us well.

1110
01:08:03,642 --> 01:08:05,519
Just know that all approvals
on Team Pro Bono

1111
01:08:05,603 --> 01:08:07,354
will go through me from now on.

1112
01:08:07,438 --> 01:08:08,647
Under someone like him,

1113
01:08:08,731 --> 01:08:10,024
Team Pro Bono can't do anything.

1114
01:08:10,107 --> 01:08:11,442
If they can't do anything,

1115
01:08:11,525 --> 01:08:12,902
I'll have to lay them off.

1116
01:08:12,985 --> 01:08:15,404
Is it weird for an attorney
to follow the firm's order?

1117
01:08:15,487 --> 01:08:16,447
I'll retain counsel.

1118
01:08:16,530 --> 01:08:18,741
I'm Oh Jung-in,
attorney for defendant Kang Da-wit.

1119
01:08:18,824 --> 01:08:21,869
Are a person's intentions that simple?

1120
01:08:21,952 --> 01:08:23,954
Is it okay for the others
to judge them so rashly?

1121
01:08:24,038 --> 01:08:27,708
If they interfere in matters they had
no authority over, no crime is committed.

1122
01:08:27,791 --> 01:08:28,792
"Not guilty."

1123
01:08:28,876 --> 01:08:31,045
I want to hear the truth from you.

1124
01:08:31,128 --> 01:08:33,339
The desire for revenge
against Yoo Baek-man.

1125
01:08:33,422 --> 01:08:36,008
Did that influence your trial?

1126
01:08:43,182 --> 01:08:45,184
Subtitle translation by: Yoon Hyewon

